HaramVeil includes or links against the following notable third-party components.

1. ONNX Runtime Android
   Artifact: com.microsoft.onnxruntime:onnxruntime-android
   License: MIT
   Upstream: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime
   Compatibility note: GPLv3-compatible.

2. Google Play Services ML Kit Text Recognition
   Artifact: com.google.android.gms:play-services-mlkit-text-recognition
   License status: distributed under Google Play Services / ML Kit terms, not an open-source Apache-2.0 AndroidX-style library
   Upstream: https://developers.google.com/ml-kit
   Compatibility note: this optional proprietary dependency should be excluded from a true F-Droid build. Recommended replacement for fully free-software distribution: ship the FOSS ONNX OCR path only.

3. AndroidX Core, Lifecycle, Navigation, Compose, WorkManager, DataStore, Security Crypto, SQLite
   License: Apache License 2.0
   Upstream: https://developer.android.com/jetpack/androidx
   Compatibility note: Apache-2.0 is GPLv3-compatible.

4. Coil
   Artifact: io.coil-kt:coil-compose
   License: Apache License 2.0
   Upstream: https://github.com/coil-kt/coil
   Compatibility note: GPLv3-compatible.

5. Bcrypt library
   Artifact: at.favre.lib:bcrypt
   License: Apache License 2.0
   Upstream: https://github.com/patrickfav/bcrypt
   Compatibility note: GPLv3-compatible.
   Additional note: this project does not currently use jBCrypt; earlier planning notes that mentioned jBCrypt no longer match the actual dependency tree.

6. SQLCipher for Android
   Artifact: net.zetetic:android-database-sqlcipher
   License: BSD-style / SQLCipher permissive license family
   Upstream: https://github.com/sqlcipher/android-database-sqlcipher
   Compatibility note: permissive and generally GPLv3-compatible.
   Additional note: upstream has deprecated this artifact in favor of sqlcipher-android. Migration is recommended before broader distribution.

7. NudeNet source repository
   Source: https://github.com/notAI-tech/NudeNet
   Repository license: AGPL-3.0
   Weights used here: https://github.com/notAI-tech/NudeNet/releases/tag/v3.4-weights
   Important note: the v3.4 weight release metadata does not publish a separate weight-file license text. Redistribution of the bundled weight files should be manually verified before F-Droid or other third-party distribution.

Summary of license compatibility for this repository:

- MIT, Apache-2.0, and BSD-style dependencies used here are generally compatible with GPLv3 distribution.
- The optional ML Kit dependency is the main release-compliance concern because it is proprietary and not suitable for a pure-FOSS F-Droid binary.
- The NudeNet repo license is visible upstream, but the bundled weight-file redistribution terms remain unclear and should be reviewed before public binary redistribution.
